'''Filchner Mountains''' is a [[mountain range]] 11&nbsp;km (7&nbsp;mi) southwest of [[Drygalski Mountains]], at the west end of the [[Orvin Mountains]] of [[Queen Maud Land]]. Discovered by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] (1938â1939), led by Capt. [[Alfred Ritscher]], and named for [[Wilhelm Filchner]], leader of the German expedition to the [[Weddell Sea]] area in 1911-12. Remapped from air photos taken by the [[Sixth Norwegian Antarctic Expedition|Norwegian Antarctic Expedition]], 1958-59.

